<br>
 In a raid situation Druids can fit well in CH chain, patch heals for casters, in the meantime nuking and doting the mobs as well as providing some nice buffs, Protection of Nine and Cabbage is very nice and that is just a start on a Druids ability.<br>
<br>
 In a group they can do the same thing, they gave up being able to blast big in exchange for being able to heal and vice versa. I havent looked through the database for all the spells so I may be mistaken but show me another class that has a good nuke, heal, dot and buffs, that is how the Druid fits into things, he brings all of those skills to a group. Combine all of those and while a Druid maybe outdone by other specialist classes, that class can not do some of the other things, ie Wizards outnuke you but we have no heals. I believe this is the way it was intended to be.<br>
<br>
 This goes for all classes except a select few but in groups there is certain roles to fill, if you need a pure healer you would not get a wizard and if you are wanting a dps machine you would not pick up another cleric. <br>
<br>
Druids have their niche in groups and a well played Druid is always welcomed in my group but most the time if a Druid is unable to find a group, it is not because of his class but his unsocial behavior. Not to be mean but most the time it is the reputation some of the Druids have built for themselves. Why do you think so many bash Druids, it is not because they are great company.<br>
<br>
 I think most of the changes in the thread are insane and over the top. If you feel some minor tweaks need to be made say that, but adding insane requests in the same thread in my mind discounts most the others. About 4 posts in is when I had enough when the Druid was upset over the mage outnuking him. Well Mages are supposed to, because they have been neglected and overlooked for a little time does not mean they are out on line now.<br>
<br>
 Druids are far from hurting and they are very useful in groups, raids and still solo about as well as they always have. Before the Mini-Ch went in, I can see they needed an upgrade in heals but right now I think Druids are far from hurting that should require some of the drastic changes that were mentioned in the post and thread. This is my opinion, maybe I am around Super-Druids that are the best Druids in EQ but I would think there is quite a few others around who use every ability a Druid has and is very happy with their class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heofmanyfals>HeOfManyFals</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 483<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 7:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thats exactly the problem</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I guess that is were my opinion for a role of a Druid and yours differ, Druids were never meant to be a specialist they sacrificed that in exchange for being the generalist and being able to do almost everything.<br>
