<br>
 In a normal exp group I am in; we have myself, lvl 65 Wizard for DPS, lvl 65 Druid for the healing, doting, buffing, some nuking and the other things he brings, lvl 65 Paladin for MA, little healing, and rez if things go sour, lvl 65 Bard for crowd control and all the other nice things bards bring( Rizlona and chorus of Marr <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), lvl 62 Rogue for more Dps, and the last spot is filled with various others, sometimes a cleric, enchanter, or any other friends who may be on at the time. I know some will say, well you are high level, most PoP spells were upgrades from earlier version, put in game to fight and use in PoP.<br>
<br>
This group does well and while not the exact Holy Trinity the exp rate is very close to the 'Perfect Trinity Group'. Sure we may have a few deaths and some downtime here and there, but all and all it is not to bad. The main thing is that it works, and works pretty well, add to the fact we all are friends and we have a good time is the main thing. <br>
<br>
I think some need to get out of the thinking of having the perfect setup and have fun. Every class has their weakness, Druids can fill quite a few roles depending on the situation. <br>
<br>
 2 classes right now, Enchanter and Cleric, are usually considered a must have, in some cases they are but because you are not considered the must have, does not mean you are broken by any means. If you like the idea of being the best at a skill, play the specialist class instead of trying to turn the Druid class into something that it was not intended to be. Just my impression on how Verant/SOE wants the Druid to fit in.<br>
<br>
 Please do not get me mistaken in far from EQ Fanboi but for the list of needs for the game, a druid being upgraded is close to the bottom. Some things I wish they would spend the time to work on before Druids is upgrading Warriors Taunt Ability, Slight Upgrade on a Rogues Damage Output, Adjusting some of the PoP loot tables. EQ is far from perfect and can be so much more but wasting time giving a class something they really do not need at this time, takes away from things they should be doing. Guess that last sentence sums up the SOE way though and Druids will get the upgrades before the other stuff gets looked at :/ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gemlin>Gemlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 486<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 9:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids are insane</span><hr size=1> Druids List Wants : <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Class spell/AA concerns: (Many of which were already mentioned here.)<br>
<br>
Request for Casting Subtlety type skill<br>
<br>
Request for Healing Adept and Healing Gift to work with all heal spells<br>
<br>
Reduce reuse timer on SotW from 22 to 5-10min<br>
<br>
Increase resist modifier on E'ci's Frosty Breath<br>
<br>
Reevaluate Harmony - best lull spell is now the worst<br>
<br>
Allow Protection of the (whatever) stack with Aego/Virtue<br>
<br>
Lower the mana cost of Karana's Renewal (500)<br>
<br>
Summon companion to work with DC creatures<br>
<br>
Remove outdoor only restrictions from spells <br>
<br>
Increase druid charm level limit from 60 to 65 (possibly as an AA skill)<br>
<br>
Change natureskin line of spells into &quot;symbol&quot; type lines, protection of the (whatever) into aego line (ie: they stack) instead of allowing aego and PotX to stack.<br>
<br>
Improve the Attack debuffs so that debuffing attack actually creates a noticable reduction in dps.<br>
<br>
Add more dire-charmable creatures - not just at entrances of zones.<br>
<br>
Improve/change Wrath of the Wild (Wrath of Booboo? - swarm of bearpets) <br>
<br>
New ability ideas:<br>
<br>
Animal-only slow<br>
<br>
AC buff vs animals only<br>
<br>
NPC damage mitigation spell (limit amount of damage outputted by a creature). Does not stack with slow spells.<br>
<br>
Attack debuff with significant reduction in attack - stacks with slow spells.<br>
<br>
Percentage based damage shields - instead of a set number, damage shield which returns a percentage of what a creature hits you for.<br>
<br>
Increase crit melee hits (short duration).<br>
<br>
Increase crit spells (short duration).<br>
<br>
Damage bonus for melee (short duration).<br>
<br>
Extremely short duration mob slow spell.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fork&quot; AA skill - % based activation (like crits) - on a successful activation, the spell acts as if two of the same spell were cast with no additional aggro, just double damage.<br>
<br>
Animal only heal over time<br>
<br>
90% rez<br>
<br>
61-65 level group wolfform or group Mask of the (whatever). Adds to attack, still gives ultravision, some mana/hp regen (+2-3). No &quot;wolf bobblehead motion&quot; if possible.<br>
<br>
Spell which allows for weapons to proc a DD<br>
<br>
&quot;Nature's Focus&quot; AA:2/4/6, When activated, adds 100/125/150% to the damage of the next DD cast, at a cost of 200% mana. Displayed as a critical blast. Prerequisite: rank 3 Spell Casting Fury. Reuse 4 or 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
Pet buff for summoned pet which makes the pet stronger depending on the number of people in the group.<br>
<br>
Translocate spells (single target version specifically mentioned)<br>
<br>
AA skill which allows specialization in a secondary skill<br>
<br>
Random %chance of converting melee dmg received into healing at a fixed rate, say a 50% return (ie say 10% chance, it will be streaky but overall would act as a dmg output reduction of 10% on mobs with say 5% becoming healing - a 50% return rate)<br>
<br>
Random %chance of converting spell/spell-like (ie breath) effects into healing, say at a 50% return (as above perhaps 10% chance, so 1x out of 10 that 1000hp aoe might be a 500hp heal).<br>
<br>
Random %chance of converting melee dmg received into MANA at a fixed rate, say 50% return. (ie a melee hit for 300 has a 10% chance of being converted into 150 mana).<br>
<br>
Random %chance of converting spell/spell-like (ie breath) effects into healing, say at a 25% return (as above perhaps 10% chance, so 1x out of 10 that 1000hp aoe might become 250 mana. Remember this nets down to 25% of 10%, so 2.5% mana return on spell dmg over time. Shouldn't be too nutty).<br>
<br>
Buffs to increase Damage Mitigation and Damage Avoidance would be nice. Maybe this would mean just adding an AC component to a spell like Nature's Recovery, but possibly a new line of defense ability increasing buffs along the lines of Combat Stability and Combat Agility.<br>
<br>
Re-evaluate the effectiveness of Enhanced/Viscid roots. Making them more reliable could give druids a useful role in groups. <br>
